MIGRATION DRIVERS & COST BREAKDOWN:
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Current Annual Operating Costs: $5.2M
├─ Licensing (VMware, Cloudera, RedHat, OpenStack): $3.65M (70%)
├─ Data Center (Power, Cooling, Space): $850K (16%)
├─ Hardware Maintenance: $450K (9%)
└─ Network & Infrastructure: $250K (5%)

Target Post-Migration Annual Costs: $3.2M
├─ GCP Compute & Storage: $2.1M
├─ GCP Licensing (committed): $850K
└─ Network egress & services: $250K

Net Annual Savings Target: $2.0M (38% reduction)

Key Migration Priorities:
1. Immediate Quick Wins: VM rightsizing, contract negotiations ($500K in 4 months)
2. Hadoop→GCS/BigQuery: Decommission Hadoop cluster ($600K/year savings)
3. VMware VMs→GCE/GKE: Reduce VMware ELA ($400K/year savings)
4. OpenShift→GKE: Eliminate OpenShift licenses ($480K/year savings)
5. OpenStack→GCE: Eliminate OpenStack support costs ($120K/year savings)
